{"type":"message","id":"7ebdaf8b","parentId":"89162bc1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:05:59.430Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8f62gluspwi8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 110515\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI Analysis just completed (found 44.8% are noise, only 5.7% have high CFI)\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key pending item is: \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete experiment that would validate or refute the CFI findings. Let me think about what this entails:\r\n\r\n1. Currently compression is frequency-based (count how often something appears)\r\n2. CFI analysis showed frequency alone is misleading - many high-frequency items are just metaprogramming artifacts\r\n3. A CFI-weighted approach would weight by CFI rather than pure frequency\r\n\r\nThe experiment should:\r\n- Take a set of invariants (from pulse files)\r\n- Compare frequency-based prediction vs CFI-weighted prediction\r\n- Measure which better predicts \"what matters in next pulse\"\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment design document that outlines this, or even better, implement a simple script that does the comparison.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the notes more carefully:\r\n- \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n\r\nThis seems like it could be a script that:\r\n1. Reads the CFI results from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n2. Compares frequency-based selection vs CFI-weighted selection\r\n3. Shows which would predict \"important\" items better\r\n\r\nLet me create a concise experiment specification/design that moves this forward. I could create a Python script that does the comparison, or a design document.\r\n\r\nGiven that I should be specific and prefer file edits, let me create an experiment design document first, then potentially a script.\r\n\r\nActually, the most impactful single action would be to start designing or implementing the CFI-weighted compression experiment. Let me create:\r\n\r\n1. An experiment design document outlining the methodology\r\n2. Perhaps a Python script skeleton that implements it\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Ensure the output goes to the research directory\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a precise experiment that can systematically test the CFI-weighted compression approach against the baseline frequency method.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), meaning frequency-based compression is heavily contaminated. A CFI-weighted experiment is needed to validate whether filtering by CFI produces better next-pulse prediction than pure frequency.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares frequency-baseline vs CFI-weighted selection on pulse file invariants, measuring which method better captures \"research trajectory\" content vs metaprogramming noise.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-based compression by filtering out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) and preserving true causal invariants (CFI>0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Data Source\r\n- Invariants from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n- Pulse files: `pulse_*.md`\r\n\r\n### Methods Compared\r\n1. **Frequency Baseline**: Top-N by occurrence count\r\n2. **CFI-Weighted**: Top-N by CFI score (ignore CFI=0)\r\n\r\n### Metric\r\n- **Coverage Score**: % of \"research trajectory\" content (CFI>0.7) captured in Top-N\r\n- **Noise Score**: % of metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) in Top-N\r\n\r\n### Expected Result\r\n| Method | Coverage | Noise |\r\n|--------|----------|-------|\r\n| Frequency | ~30-40% | ~45% |\r\n| CFI-Weighted | ~85-95% | <5% |\r\n\r\n## Script: `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py`\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"Compare frequency vs CFI-weighted compression on pulse invariants.\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef load_cfi_results():\r\n    \"\"\"Parse CFI_RESULTS.md for invariant data.\"\"\"\r\n    # TODO: Implement parsing\r\n    pass\r\n\r\ndef frequency_selection(invariants, n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Select top-N by frequency count.\"\"\"\r\n    sorted_inv = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x['count'], reverse=True)\r\n    return sorted_inv[:n]\r\n\r\ndef cfi_weighted_selection(invariants, n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Select top-N by CFI score, filter CFI=0.\"\"\"\r\n    filtered = [i for i in invariants if i['cfi'] > 0]\r\n    sorted_inv = sorted(filtered, key=lambda x: x['cfi'], reverse=True)\r\n    return sorted_inv[:n]\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_selection(selection):\r\n    \"\"\"Calculate coverage and noise scores.\"\"\"\r\n    total = len(selection)\r\n    high_cfi = sum(1 for i in selection if i['cfi'] >= 0.7)\r\n    zero_cfi = sum(1 for i in selection if i['cfi'] == 0)\r\n    return {\r\n        'coverage': high_cfi / total if total > 0 else 0,\r\n        'noise': zero_cfi / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    invariants = load_cfi_results()\r\n    \r\n    freq_top20 = frequency_selection(invariants, n=20)\r\n    cfi_top20 = cfi_weighted_selection(invariants, n=20)\r\n    \r\n    freq_metrics = evaluate_selection(freq_top20)\r\n    cfi_metrics = evaluate_selection(cfi_top20)\r\n    \r\n    print(\"Frequency Baseline:\", freq_metrics)\r\n    print(\"CFI-Weighted:     \", cfi_metrics)\r\n    \r\n    # Output to results file\r\n    results = {\r\n        'frequency_baseline': freq_metrics,\r\n        'cfi\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:05:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774364759427}}
